backslashUpgraded

private boolean backslashUpgraded
The flag indicates that the back slashes are converted. In older MX versions double back slashes was escaped. In this cases all escaped double back slashes must be replaced. In newer MX versions this 'feature' does not exists anymore if an MQL insert was done.

See Also:
parse(String,String), write(ParameterCache_mxJPO, Appendable)

update

protected void update(ParameterCache_mxJPO _paramCache,
                      CharSequence _preMQLCode,
                      CharSequence _postMQLCode,
                      CharSequence _preTCLCode,
                      Map<String,String> _tclVariables,
                      File _sourceFile)
               throws Exception
The method overwrites the original method to append the MQL statements in the _preMQLCode to update this JPO program. Following steps are done within update:
  • An existing execute user is removed.
  • Execution of the JPO is immediate.
  • The description is set to an empty string.
  • The JPO program is set to not hidden.
  • The JPO program does not need the context of a business object.
  • The MQL program is not downloadable.
  • The input / output of the MQL program is not piped.
  • The MQL program is not pooled (used only for TCL programs).
  • The JPO is updated with the content of _sourceFile.
  • Embedded TCL update code is searched depending on the file extension and the TCL update needed parameter PARAM_NEEDED. If for a file extension a line prefix is defined, the line prefix is removed from the TCL update code (and also the mark texts defined with PARAM_MARKSTART and PARAM_MARKEND depends on the line prefix).

Overrides:
update in class AbstractAdminObject_mxJPO
Parameters:
_paramCache - parameter cache
_preMQLCode - MQL statements which must be called before the TCL code is executed
_postMQLCode - MQL statements which must be called after the TCL code is executed
_preTCLCode - TCL code which is defined before the source file is sourced
_tclVariables - map of all TCL variables where the key is the name and the value is value of the TCL variable (the value is automatically converted to TCL syntax!)
_sourceFile - souce file with the TCL code to update
Throws:
Exception - if the update from derived class failed
See Also:
PARAM_MARKEND, PARAM_MARKSTART, PARAM_NEEDED
